originalText.text: Good location to our hotel but check in process for my car and check out was horrid. The guy when we got there was not clear about what we should do and really rushed us. Did not pay attention to our reservation at all. When I came to pick up the car at said time that I paid until, I was asked for a ticket which I couldn't find in my bag and honestly didn't remember getting because of the experience the day before. The guy was NOT going to get my car for me even though I calmly suggested using my registration to prove it's my car. As well as all the other information I can prove it's my car including the reservation information and QR code . He just kept saying "no ticket" "no car" I was incredible close to calling the police. He kept giving me attitude so I dumped out my entire purse on the ground and finally found a tiny white ticket. HORRIBLE customer service at this location.

originalText.text: Parking attendant touched my butt twice. First time I brushed it off as a mistake, second time it was clear it was intentional. Then as I was pulling off he stuck his head in the window— no mask— and asked where I was going. Yikes.

originalText.text: I have been using iPark for my parking needs and I am never disappointed. originalText.text:
Don’t park here. They lost the keys to someone before me which I prob should have taken as a sign to find somewhere else but lesson learned.

Still decided park cuz it was close to the hotel. When I left my car, explicitly asked whether I need to call ahead to get my car and they said “nope, just come.” Well, here I am in line behind a woman that said no one’s been there for the last 45 mins.

Looking around the walls, I see a sign that says you have to give 1 hour’s notice to get your car.

Screw you John Heras, Supervisor.
